PRESIDENT RECEP TAYYIP ERDOGAN faces increasing pressures at home and abroad, and he’s adding to them—most of all by acquiring Russian missile defences that make Turkey’s NATO allies nervous. As Colombia emerges from a half-century of conflict with FARC rebels, a government push aims to stem cocaine production; so far, it’s not going well. And, we examine the retirement homes for elderly LGBT people that are cropping up. Runtime: 22 min    Listen on: Apple Podcasts | Spotify | Google | Stitcher | TuneIn